<br>
&quot;As the intra-western war continues, his prediction may yet come true.  'No doubt, time is working for us,' Saddam told the Egyptian weekly al-Usbou in November.  'We have to buy some more time, and the American-British coalition will disintegrate.'&quot;<br>
<br>
Hussein is counting on the very principles of a free society to preserve his regime.  I do not know how much clearly I can make the point that dissenters, with intention or not, are helping to preserve Hussein's regime.  In fact, he is counting on YOU to help delay military action.<br>
<br>
But that is the way of our society and our rules.  So be it.  I just wish people would see the consequences of their words.  But isn't that what dissenters want after all?  A peaceful solution?  Right, thanks for allying with the enemy.<br>
