<br>
I'll tell you why.  Sadamm is playing a game of international chicken where, if he can show partial compliance (destroying six (!) al-Samoun missiles in one day? WTF is that?  There are hundreds of them and it takes a whole day to destroy six?) he buys time.  And time works in your favor when a force of several thousand are sitting at your door step and in a matter of weeks the temperature, where these forces are located, will reach 120 degrees.  In fact, anything that anyone can do to prolong military action works in the dictator's favor.  Do you see the connection between protestors (I'll stop using the term &quot;dissent&quot; since it clearly takes away from our little discussion) and buying time?  May I remind you of the quote above from Sadamm saying time works in his favor and further saying that in time the US/UK coalition will disintegrate?  Can you see the similarity between his quote and yours saying &quot;I don't care how long it takes.&quot;  You, my dear online friend, are playing the enemy's hand.<br>
